## Input Validation

### ❌ NEVER do this:
```python
# Trusting raw input
@router.post("/")
def create_item(data: dict):  # No validation!
    db.execute(f"INSERT INTO items VALUES ('{data['name']}')")
```

### ✅ ALWAYS do this:
```python
# Pydantic validation
from pydantic import BaseModel, Field, validator

class ItemCreate(BaseModel):
    name: str = Field(min_length=1, max_length=255)
    description: str | None = Field(default=None, max_length=5000)
    
    @validator('name')
    def sanitize_name(cls, v):
        return v.strip()

@router.post("/", response_model=ItemRead)
def create_item(item: ItemCreate, repo: ItemRepository = Depends()):
    return repo.create(item)
```

